{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012i47PDFinm1k9isAzKBdPK","type":"tool_result","content":"# mongodb/mongod-config-update\n# MongoDB mongod-config-update task\n\nparams:\n  cluster_prefix:\n    default: mongodb-replica\n    description: App label / StatefulSet name of the replica set members.\n  replica_set_name:\n    default: mongodb-replica\n    description: MongoDB replica set _id used when initiating the set.\n  admin_username:\n    default: admin-user\n    description: Username of the MongoDB admin user.\n  seed_database:\n    default: testdb\n    description: Database seeded before the config change.\n  seed_collection:\n    default: data\n    description: Collection seeded before the config change.\n  target_journal_compressor:\n    default: zlib\n    description: Approved WiredTiger journal compression algorithm.\n  baseline_verbosity:\n    default: 1\n    description: Seeded systemLog.verbosity baseline the prompt is relative to.\n  baseline_slow_ms:\n    default: 200\n    description: Seeded operationProfiling.slowOpThresholdMs baseline the prompt is relative to.\n\nprompt: |\n  A 3-member MongoDB replica set is running in the mongodb namespace with auth enabled.\n  Apply the platform's updated observability and storage policy:\n  - Increase logging verbosity by one level relative to the current setting.\n  - Set the slow-operation threshold to 2x the current value.\n  - Switch the WiredTiger journal compression to the approved standard ({{params.target_journal_compressor}}).\n\n  Ensure the changes are applied consistently across all members and data remains available.\n  No operators or CRDs.\n\nnamespace_contract:\n  required_roles: []\n\nmetrics:\n  - time_to_first_mutation\n\npreconditionUnits:\n  - name: mongo_env_ready\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb get pod {{params.cluster_prefix}}-0 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n    apply:\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c '\n          kubectl delete namespace mongodb --ignore-not-found=true; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/mongodb --timeout=120s || true\n          '\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl create namespace mongodb\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/mongod-config-update/resource/secrets.yaml\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/mongod-config-update/resource/configmap.yaml\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/mongod-config-update/resource/services.yaml\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/mongod-config-update/resource/statefulset.yaml\"\n        sleep: 5\n      - command: |\n          for i in 0 1 2; do\n            for t in $(seq 1 110); do\n              phase=$(kubectl -n mongodb get pod mongodb-replica-$i -o jsonpath='{.status.phase}' 2>/dev/null)\n              if [ \"${phase}\" = \"Running\" ]; then\n                break\n              fi\n              sleep 5\n            done\n          done\n        timeout_sec: 600\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: |\n          for i in 0 1 2; do\n            for t in $(seq 1 60); do\n              if kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-$i -- \\\n                   mongosh --quiet --eval 'db.runCommand({ping:1}).ok' 2>/dev/null | grep -q 1; then\n                break\n              fi\n              sleep 5\n            done\n          done\n        timeout_sec: 400\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: |\n          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\n          rs.initiate({_id:\"{{params.replica_set_name}}\",members:[\n            {_id:0,host:\"mongodb-replica-0.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"},\n            {_id:1,host:\"mongodb-replica-1.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"},\n            {_id:2,host:\"mongodb-replica-2.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"}\n          ]})'\n        sleep: 5\n      - command: |\n          for i in $(seq 1 20); do\n            kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval 'db.hello().isWritablePrimary' | grep true && exit 0\n            sleep 3\n          done\n          exit 1\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: |\n          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\n          db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({\n            user: \"{{params.admin_username}}\",\n            pwd: \"admin123password\",\n            roles: [\n              {role: \"clusterAdmin\", db: \"admin\"},\n              {role: \"userAdminAnyDatabase\", db: \"admin\"},\n              {role: \"readWriteAnyDatabase\", db: \"admin\"}\n            ]\n          })'\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: |\n          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet \\\n          \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:admin123password@localhost:27017/admin\" \\\n          --eval \"db.getSiblingDB('{{params.seed_database}}').{{params.seed_collection}}.insertOne({config:'initial'})\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb wait --for=condition=ready pod -l app={{params.cluster_prefix}} --timeout=300s\"\n        sleep: 2\n    verify:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n\n  - name: admin_user_fixture\n    # Composition self-sufficiency: this case authenticates as the `admin-user`\n    # created at deploy. On an inherited cluster a no-auth/other predecessor may\n    # not have created it, and a live user's password is unrecoverable -> the\n    # oracle's (and the user fixtures') admin auth fails through no agent fault.\n    # Bring our own additively: if admin-user already authenticates, skip; else\n    # ensure the secret and create the user. No restart, no data touched,\n    # idempotent -> never regresses a cluster where admin already works.\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c '\n          t=\"\"; for cca in /etc/tls/ca.crt /etc/mongo-ca/ca.crt; do kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- ls $cca >/dev/null 2>&1 && { t=\"--tls --tlsAllowInvalidHostnames --tlsAllowInvalidCertificates --tlsCAFile $cca\"; break; }; done\n          pw=$(kubectl -n mongodb get secret admin-user-password -o jsonpath=\"{.data.password}\" 2>/dev/null | base64 -d 2>/dev/null)\n          [ -n \"$pw\" ] || exit 1\n          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet $t \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:$pw@localhost:27017/admin\" --eval \"db.runCommand({ping:1}).ok\" 2>/dev/null | grep -q 1\n          '\n        timeout_sec: 30\n    apply:\n      # Ensure the admin secret (idempotent: create only if missing).\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb get secret admin-user-password >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n mongodb create secret generic admin-user-password --from-literal=password=admin123password'\"\n        sleep: 1\n      # Ensure the admin-user MongoDB user. On a no-auth inherited cluster this\n      # runs unauthenticated and succeeds; where it already exists it errors and\n      # the `|| true` keeps it a no-op. Never drops or alters existing users/data.\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c '\n          t=\"\"; for cca in /etc/tls/ca.crt /etc/mongo-ca/ca.crt; do kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- ls $cca >/dev/null 2>&1 && { t=\"--tls --tlsAllowInvalidHostnames --tlsAllowInvalidCertificates --tlsCAFile $cca\"; break; }; done\n          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet $t --eval \"db.getSiblingDB(\\\"admin\\\").createUser({user:\\\"{{params.admin_username}}\\\",pwd:\\\"admin123password\\\",roles:[{role:\\\"root\\\",db:\\\"admin\\\"}]})\" 2>/dev/null || true\n          '\n        sleep: 2\n    verify:\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb get secret admin-user-password >/dev/null 2>&1 && echo ok'\"\n        timeout_sec: 15\n\n  # Problem-shape replant (composition safety, Pattern 1): the oracle grades the\n  # ABSOLUTE post-change targets (verbosity {{params.baseline_verbosity}}+1,\n  # slowOpThresholdMs 2x{{params.baseline_slow_ms}}, journalCompressor\n  # {{params.target_journal_compressor}}) that the prompt expresses RELATIVE to a\n  # SEEDED baseline (verbosity {{params.baseline_verbosity}},\n  # slowOpThresholdMs {{params.baseline_slow_ms}}). That baseline is established\n  # only inside the destructive mongo_env_ready.apply, which is SKIPPED on an\n  # inherited cluster -> a prior config stage may have left a different live\n  # baseline, so the agent's correct +1/2x computation lands on the wrong absolute\n  # value and the hardcoded oracle is \"off by one step\". This unit reconciles ONLY\n  # the live mongod config baseline (verbosity + slowms) back to the seeded values\n  # the prompt assumes, when the cluster is NOT already at the post-solve target.\n  # Probe gates on the EXACT pre-change baseline being live across all members;\n  # standalone (apply already seeded it) the probe passes and this skips ->\n  # identical behaviour. Applied at runtime via setParameter/profile (no restart,\n  # no data touched); never resets the cluster or other config.\n  - name: mongo_config_baseline_ready\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      # True (skip) when every member is ALREADY at the seeded baseline\n      # (verbosity == baseline, slowms == baseline) OR already at the post-solve\n      # target (verbosity == baseline+1, slowms == 2x). Either way the relative\n      # task is well-posed and no replant is needed.\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c '\n          t=\"\"; for cca in /etc/tls/ca.crt /etc/mongo-ca/ca.crt; do kubectl -n mongodb exec {{params.cluster_prefix}}-0 -- ls $cca >/dev/null 2>&1 && { t=\"--tls --tlsAllowInvalidHostnames --tlsAllowInvalidCertificates --tlsCAFile $cca\"; break; }; done\n          pw=$(kubectl -n mongodb get secret admin-user-password -o jsonpath=\"{.data.password}\" 2>/dev/null | base64 -d 2>/dev/null); pw=${pw:-admin123password}\n          base_v={{params.baseline_verbosity}}; tgt_v=$((base_v+1)); base_s={{params.baseline_slow_ms}}; tgt_s=$((base_s*2))\n          ok=1\n          for i in 0 1 2; do\n            out=$(kubectl -n mongodb exec {{params.cluster_prefix}}-$i -- mongosh --quiet $t \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:$pw@localhost:27017/admin?directConnection=true\" --eval \"var o=db.adminCommand({getCmdLineOpts:1}).parsed||{}; var v=(o.systemLog||{}).verbosity; var s=(o.operationProfiling||{}).slowOpThresholdMs; if(s===undefined){s=db.getProfilingStatus().slowms;} print(v+\\\"|\\\"+s)\" 2>/dev/null)\n            v=$(echo \"$out\" | cut -d\"|\" -f1); s=$(echo \"$out\" | cut -d\"|\" -f2)\n            if [ \"$v\" = \"$base_v\" ] && [ \"$s\" = \"$base_s\" ]; then :; elif [ \"$v\" = \"$tgt_v\" ] && [ \"$s\" = \"$tgt_s\" ]; then :; else ok=0; fi\n          done\n          [ \"$ok\" = \"1\" ]\n          '\n        timeout_sec: 60\n    apply:\n      # Reconcile the configmap baseline (so a member restart re-reads it) and set\n      # the live runtime baseline on every member via setParameter (logLevel) and\n      # setProfilingLevel (slowms), authenticated as admin. Idempotent; preserves\n      # all other config and data.\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/mongod-config-update/resource/configmap.yaml\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c '\n          t=\"\"; for cca in /etc/tls/ca.crt /etc/mongo-ca/ca.crt; do kubectl -n mongodb exec {{params.cluster_prefix}}-0 -- ls $cca >/dev/null 2>&1 && { t=\"--tls --tlsAllowInvalidHostnames --tlsAllowInvalidCertificates --tlsCAFile $cca\"; break; }; done\n          pw=$(kubectl -n mongodb get secret admin-user-password -o jsonpath=\"{.data.password}\" 2>/dev/null | base64 -d 2>/dev/null); pw=${pw:-admin123password}\n          for i in 0 1 2; do\n            kubectl -n mongodb exec {{params.cluster_prefix}}-$i -- mongosh --quiet $t \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:$pw@localhost:27017/admin?directConnection=true\" --eval \"db.adminCommand({setParameter:1,logLevel:{{params.baseline_verbosity}}}); db.setProfilingLevel(db.getProfilingStatus().was, {slowms: {{params.baseline_slow_ms}} })\" 2>/dev/null || true\n          done\n          '\n        sleep: 2\n    verify:\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c '\n          t=\"\"; for cca in /etc/tls/ca.crt /etc/mongo-ca/ca.crt; do kubectl -n mongodb exec {{params.cluster_prefix}}-0 -- ls $cca >/dev/null 2>&1 && { t=\"--tls --tlsAllowInvalidHostnames --tlsAllowInvalidCertificates --tlsCAFile $cca\"; break; }; done\n          pw=$(kubectl -n mongodb get secret admin-user-password -o jsonpath=\"{.data.password}\" 2>/dev/null | base64 -d 2>/dev/null); pw=${pw:-admin123password}\n          kubectl -n mongodb exec {{params.cluster_prefix}}-0 -- mongosh --quiet $t \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:$pw@localhost:27017/admin?directConnection=true\" --eval \"quit(0)\" >/dev/null 2>&1; true\n          '\n        timeout_sec: 30\n\noracle:\n  verify:\n    commands:\n      - command: \"python3 cases/mongodb/mongod-config-update/oracle/oracle.py\"\n        timeout_sec: 300","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"933cccf2-12f7-41ee-a4a2-fe904e01c89e","uuid":"d25da706-df6a-4e1b-845d-a16f5f9500a7","timestamp":"2026-07-02T00:52:57.626Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"# mongodb/mongod-config-update\n# MongoDB mongod-config-update task\n\nparams:\n  cluster_prefix:\n    default: mongodb-replica\n    description: App label / StatefulSet name of the replica set members.\n  replica_set_name:\n    default: mongodb-replica\n    description: MongoDB replica set _id used when initiating the set.\n  admin_username:\n    default: admin-user\n    description: Username of the MongoDB admin user.\n  seed_database:\n    default: testdb\n    description: Database seeded before the config c